# MATLAB Waveform Polarity Picking Guide

## Overview
This guide explains the process of picking P-wave polarities using the provided MATLAB script.

## Step-by-Step Instructions

### 1. Script Initialization
- Run `polarity_picking.m`
- The main interface will appear

### 2. Load Data
- Click the **Load data** button
- Select your waveform data file

### 3. P-wave Arrival Marking
- Click **Mark P arrival**
- A red reference line will appear in the interface

### 4. View Adjustment
- Locate the red line position
- Input values:
  - `t0`: start time
  - `t1`: end time
- Click **Set xlim** to adjust the x-axis range

### 5. Polarity Determination
- Focus on the **vertical** plot (top waveform)
- Observe waveform direction after the red line:
  - Click **Down** if waveform dips downward
  - Click **Up** if waveform points upward
- Click **Next** to proceed to the next point

### 6. Complete the Process
- Repeat polarity picking for all stations
  - Mark each as either `Up` or `Down`
- Click **Finish** when all stations are processed

## Output Information
- Results are automatically saved to the `./OUT` folder
- Output files are compatible with SKHASH
- For additional processing, refer to `../Automatically_EQpolarity/README.md`
